# Potentiometer & Button

## Reading a Potentiometer
ESP32 ADCs are 12-bit (0-4095).

```cpp
void setup() {
  Serial.begin(115200);
}
void loop() {
  int val = analogRead(34);
  Serial.println(val);
  delay(10);
}
```

## Reading a Button
Use internal pullups to avoid external resistors.

```cpp
void setup() {
  pinMode(14, INPUT_PULLUP);
}
void loop() {
  if (digitalRead(14) == LOW) {
    Serial.println("Pressed!");
  }
}
```

# Rotary Encoders

Encoders allow infinite rotation. Use the ESP32Encoder library for best performance.

## Wiring
- CLK -> GPIO 25
- DT -> GPIO 26
- SW -> GPIO 27

## Code Example
```cpp
#include <ESP32Encoder.h>
ESP32Encoder encoder;
void setup() {
  encoder.attachHalfQuad(26, 25);
  encoder.setCount(0);
}
void loop() {
  Serial.println(encoder.getCount());
}
```

# 0.96" OLED Display (I2C)

Commonly found as 4-pin modules (VCC, GND, SDA, SCL).

## Wiring
- SDA -> GPIO 21
- SCL -> GPIO 22
- VCC -> 3.3V

## Library
Use **Adafruit SSD1306** and **Adafruit GFX**.

```cpp
#include <Adafruit_SSD1306.h>
Adafruit_SSD1306 display(128, 64, &Wire, -1);
void setup() {
  display.begin(SSD1306_SWITCHCAPVCC, 0x3C);
  display.clearDisplay();
  display.setTextSize(1);
  display.setTextColor(WHITE);
  display.setCursor(0,0);
  display.println("Hello World");
  display.display();
}
```

# ESP32 WiFi Station

Connect your ESP32 to the internet.

```cpp
#include <WiFi.h>
const char* ssid = "NetworkName";
const char* password = "Password";

void setup() {
  Serial.begin(115200);
  WiFi.begin(ssid, password);
  while (WiFi.status() != WL_CONNECTED) {
    delay(500);
    Serial.print(".");
  }
  Serial.println(WiFi.localIP());
}
```

# Bluetooth Serial

The easiest way to talk to a phone/PC wirelessly.

```cpp
#include "BluetoothSerial.h"
BluetoothSerial SerialBT;

void setup() {
  SerialBT.begin("ESP32_Device");
}

void loop() {
  if (SerialBT.available()) {
    Serial.write(SerialBT.read());
  }
}
```
